        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The addition of the consumption volumes in the US in 2002 (from USGS, 2002 Pesticide use Maps) of the [thio]carbamate-compounds aldicarb, asulam, carbaryl, carbofuran, cycloate, desmedipham, EPTC, formetanate HCl, indoxacarb, metam-sodium, methomyl, molinate, oxamyl, pebulate, phenmedipham, propamocarb, thiobencarb, thiodicarb, triallate has been used to estimate the production volumes of this type of pesticide in the world. For that, it has been extrapolated to a Global production mix using the ha of Arable land and Permanent crops of US versus the ha of Arable land and Permanent crops in the world in 2002 (1514/179 million ha; FAOSTAT).</productionVolumeComment>
